About Link Intersystems - Commons

Link Intersystems commons (lis) is a collection of reusable software components based on pure Java.

Project Modules

This project has declared the following modules:

Name Description
Math Link Intersystems Commons Math (lis-commons-math) is a reusable software library that provides support for simple common mathematical related tasks.
Lang Link Intersystems Commons Lang (lis-commons-lang) is a library that provides reusable software components based on Java core features under the java.lang package and sub-packages.
Lang Criteria Link Intersystems Commons Lang Criteria (lis-commons-lang-criteria) is a library that provides a criteria api for reflection related tasks.
Beans Link Intersystems Commons Beans (lis-commons-beans) is a collection of reusable software components that provide a simpler programming api for the Java beans api.
Util Link Intersystems Commons Util (lis-commons-util) is collection of reusable software components that extend the standard java.util components.
lis-commons-test Link Intersystems commons (lis) is a collection of reusable software components based on pure Java.
Graph Link Intersystems Commons Graph (lis-commons-graph) is a collection of reusable software components that provide support for graph and tree related programming tasks, such as models and search algorithms.
Events Link Intersystems Commons Events (lis-commons-events) is a collection of reusable software components that provide support for event and event listener based programming tasks.
lis-commons-jdbc Link Intersystems commons (lis) is a collection of reusable software components based on pure Java.
lis-commons-test-db Link Intersystems commons (lis) is a collection of reusable software components based on pure Java.
